parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight switch wiring harness can cause a fire in the instrument panel, potentially leading to injuries, property damage, and vehicle destruction.
symptoms: Smoke or flames emanating from the instrument panel
burning odor inside the vehicle
melted instrument panel liner
damaged front carpet
scorched front seats
cracked front windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-lock brake system can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to fly open while driving, obstructing the driver's view, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The hood latch comes loose
the hood flies up while driving
the windshield is damaged
the hood is unable to stay closed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure to Notify Vehicle Owners of Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to notify vehicle owners of a recall can lead to delayed or missed repairs, potentially causing safety issues or accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle owners are not informed of recalls
dealerships claim incorrect addresses
dealerships refuse to perform repairs
vehicle owners are referred to district managers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooling line connector can cause transmission fluid to leak, leading to overheating and damage to the transmission, which can result in costly repairs, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaking from the cooling line connector
transmission overheating
difficulty shifting gears
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exclusion of this vehicle from the recall may lead to the owner being unaware of the potential issue, resulting in delayed or lack of necessary repairs, which can cause further damage to the transmission and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: None
as this issue is related to the recall process rather than a specific vehicle symptom.
